# stpDMIRTranspariz\_Step4\_1 and stpDMIRTranspariz\_Step4\_2

## Process logic

* In Step 4.1, compute portfolio-level AUM-based metrics for inventory level 0 and update relevant fields in the working table.
* In Step 4.2, for inventory levels 1–5, compute update and insert branches based on underlying portfolio structure, NAV dates, and hierarchical prefixes.
* Merge update and insert branches into the working table with computed fields and updated modification timestamps.

## Tables Used as Inputs

|           Table Name          |                                                  Description                                                 |
| :---------------------------: | :----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------: |
| `DMIR.tblDMIRTransparizLTWrk` |   Core look‑through working table containing portfolio holdings, AUM, NAV dates, currency rates, and flags.  |
|  `DMIR.stpDWAUAuditId()` (fn) | Scalar function that returns a new audit identifier for tracking changes across runs. (not a physical table) |

---

## Tables Used as Target

|           Table Name          |                                                                                                                                            Description                                                                                                                                           |
| :---------------------------: | :----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------: |
| `DMIR.tblDMIRTransparizLTWrk` | The same working table is both read from and written back to. Final computed columns are upserted into this table: <br> - `numHoldValueInReportPortfCur` <br> - `numPctReportPortfInUndrlyg` <br> - `numWeightedAmtInReportPortf` <br> - `numWeightedQtqInReportPortf` <br> - `datLastModifDate` |

---

## Temporary (Staging) Tables

|    Temporary Table   |                                                                     Purpose / Description                                                                     | Equivalent Pandas DataFrame |
| :------------------: | :-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------: | :-------------------------: |
|  `#tmpMaster_step41` |     Holds the joined “master” rows (filtered to one `InventoryLevel`) with lookup AUM (highest AUM per partition) and newly computed metrics for Step 4.1.    |         `df_joined`         |
| `#tmpMaster_step421` | Holds the “update branch” for a given `InventoryLevel`: applies AUM (smallest per partition), LYG aggregation, computes updated metrics for Step 4.2 updates. |      `df_update_branch`     |
| `#tmpMaster_step422` |   Holds the “insert branch” for a given `InventoryLevel`: identifies rows to insert (when previous level is null or flags indicate missing underlying data).  |      `df_insert_branch`     |

---

